    {
      "explanation": "When you checked factories, building sites, stores, and clinics first, you were practicing sectoral comparison. That broader scan stopped you from mistaking one weak industry for the whole economy.",
      "name": "Sectoral Comparison"
    },
    {
      "explanation": "When you lined up metro, small-town, and border-area data, you were reading regional comovements. The pattern mattered because some places moved together while others lagged or led.",
      "name": "Regional Comovements"
