      "minStrongChoices": 3,
      "narrative": "You give a mostly solid briefing with a few gaps still showing. The audience understands the big direction, but some counties and sectors need more explanation than you had time to give.",
      "title": "Mostly Right"
    },
    {
      "minStrongChoices": 1,
      "narrative": "You catch part of the pattern, but some of the state’s differences stay blurred. The briefing makes sense in pieces, yet people keep asking how one county can boom while another stalls.",
      "title": "Half the Map"
    },
    {
      "minStrongChoices": 0,
      "narrative": "You lean on one number or one region and the story collapses under questions. That rough outcome still teaches the key lesson: this economy moves differently across sectors and places, so one headline can’t carry it all.",
      "title": "One Number"
    }
  ]
}
